In the bustling port of **Marisvel**, where ships carried both gold and lies, there lived a merchant named **Dain**, whose wealth was built on hollow promises. He sold mirrors that did not reflect faces, but **whispers of the future**—for a price. One day, a young fisherman, **Toren**, traded his father’s last boat for one of Dain’s mirrors, hoping to see his lost love’s return.

