The cycle ended not with mercy, but with **exposure**. Dain, unable to bear his own reflection, shattered every mirror in his shop. But the curse followed him—his own shadow now whispered his sins, and his hands, once greedy, could no longer hold coin without burning. The people of Marisvel learned that **truth, like the tide, always returns**, and Dain’s greed became a warning carved into the docks: *‘What you take with lies, the sea will claim in truth.’*"
